TestLiteralArrayElementsAreData
/ set %list% = [1, "two"] — both elements are Data carrying their type tag
/ (number, text), not raw primitives. %list[0]% = 1, %list[1]% = "two". After
/ Stage 3, every list element is a Data — the [raw, Data] split is gone.
- set %list% = [1, "two"]
- assert %list[0]% equals 1
- assert %list[1]% equals "two"
